        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 5:45PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 33 miles north of Calion to 7 miles
south of Junction City, or extending from 35 miles northeast of
Smackover to 7 miles south of Junction City, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
El Dorado, Smackover, Norphlet, Huttig, Junction City, Strong,
Calion, Emerson, Wesson, Lisbon, Lawson, Urbana, Mount Holly,
Village, Atlanta, Lapile, Felsenthal, Newell and Catesville.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
